Tom Esch Reading 06

https://www.thewindowsclub.com/windows-defender-security-center 

Introduces the task bar Shield connecting the user to Windows Security Center settings. The window operates as a settings dashboard for:
Virus and threat protection
Launch 3rd party app; Controlled Folder Access
Account protection
Account and sign-in credentials and security
Firewall and network protection
Manages and helps troubleshoot network 
App and Browser Control
Settings for SmartScreen
Device Security
Built-in security
Device Performance and Health
Monitors battery life and drive storage
Driver and other system update info
Great resource for trouble-shooting issues
Family Options
Parental controls
